nts1.d: "A show dedicated to the L.A. sunsets and all the hard working people who keep this city going & who defend it against pinches culeros…u know who."
Naomi Asa on the NTS airwaves, delivering soothing soul and spiritual jazz.

Los Angeles-based artist and filmmaker Arthur Jafa graces the NTS signal for an hour of varied sounds spanning soul classics, chopped and screwed tracks, his own edits and recordings. 
Jafa joins his peer across the Atlantic, Mark Leckey for HARDCORE / LOVE, a joint showcase at the Whitgift Centre, Croydon, presented by Conditions.  Running until 10th August, 2025.
Special guest shows from around the world.

Atmospheric, complex, and influential drum and bass productions from Source Direct, the former duo that distinguished themselves as luminaries in breakbeat science in the mid-1990s.

Zurich-based Jenny Cara brings the heat with a blend of cheerful and hard-hitting house, creating a space that celebrates community, history, and pure energy.
Fusing the nostalgic, niche & the ‘nu A.G’. London’s best kept secret is back. Blends on brains off!

International portal for contemporary pop, leaning into the autotuned future… from the mind of Christopher Kirkley, the mastermind behind record label Sahel Sounds.
From the host: "Tanzanian Kwaya (choir) music from early 2000s VCDS. Polyphonic harmonies, drum machines, and synthesizers, in some of the standout Swahili Gospel tracks. All found on Youtube, with heavy nostalgia in the comment sections."

nts2.d: the moment when you're waking up and your brain is still quiet, right before the day begins. we arrive from a peaceful sleep into collision with whatever today's world will bring. in that peaceful place, where fears/worries/wars don't live. then it's just another day…

the good kind of nowhere, watching the day like it's someone else's problem, presence without eye contact. half-unpacked with nowhere to be, still carrying yesterday's sun in your shoulders. keep it smooth

nts2.n: THE AESTHETICS OF EASE W/ PLUMDOSE
nts2.d: A celebration of simple, profound moments of serenity, in which emotions are conducted by the unobtrusive orchestra of the senses and the mind is uneventful. Dancing colors of soap bubbles. Fabric swaying in tender winds. Fingers gliding along wrapped arms. First bite of an orange. The sound of rolling pebbles underwater. Sleeping spirits of the room.

nts2.n: What Time Is It There? w/ Oscar & Imogen
nts2.d: A deep global exploration of music. Focusing on the freedom from disturbance and feelings of tranquility, filtered through the sounds of spiritual jazz, ambience and avant-folk.

nts2.n: House of All Words w/ Tunisian Naive Society
nts2.d:
On the edge of reality, Tunisian Naive Society explores the naive transcience of dreams through music, field recordings and recorded conversations.
Join your hosts, Emily Sarsam and Yassine Rachidi, for an hour of sonic refuge, where we explore sounds that soothe the mind, body & soul.

'Seasgair' a beautiful Scottish Gaelic word, in English it translates to dry, cozy and snug but the literal translation does not do it justice… Some of this music and these audio extracts will hopefully explain it better.

To me, peace is a calm and beautiful state. However, on our journey towards it, we often lose something or someone. Having peace means reflecting on the past and looking to the future. This may involve reflecting on what you have lost, which can be sad, but it also involves looking forward to what comes next. That's why I associate peace with melancholic yet beautiful melodies.

“The attitude toward time and environment known as ‘multitasking’ does not represent civilisational progress… Human beings in the late-modern society of work and information are not the only ones capable of multitasking.”
“The society of labouring and achievement is not a free society. It generates new constraints. Ultimately … one is simultaneously prisoner and guard, victim and perpetrator. One exploits oneself.”
“The true antidote to exhaustion … is reclaiming the right to stop.”
Byung‑Chul Han
Stay peaceful - M
loops folding back into themselves, reverb smoothing the edges. a quiet spiral: peace as a pattern of repetition.
Atmospheric breaks and beats, hazy sample chops, and ambient soundscapes. Selects to let the mind drift.
Dissolve the self into everything. Breathe, relax, and resonate with the world around you. Ground the body in space and time, find peace. You are here, we are here, we are one.

nts2.n: Your Healing Hands W/ Moral Compass
nts2.d: Sonic visions for a transformative future. Let it all wash over you, arms outstretched and willing. Peace is in the palm of your hand.

A selection of songs from the Innovative Communication label after Klaus Schulze’s departure, during the new age years. I chose a few of my IC favorites that bring me a sense of peace, lets my mind wander, and at times, reminds me of the zoo. Enjoy.

subtle.d:
DJ & Producer, B-Say has been a Subtle resident DJ for over 3 years.

His radio shows tend to focus on the 140 bass music scene and aims to showcase unreleased/forthcoming music from upcoming artists, as well as premiering his own unreleased material. 

More recently B-Say has ventured out from solely DJ'ing Dubstep, with his bi-monthly 'Dub & Steppers Show' which he uses to premier his own productions.

Slick is a London-based Producer and DJ combining the sounds of Grime and Drill.
Expect sets to span from sparse wave and weightless to classic NY and UK Drill, with everything in between
J:KENZO is a producer and record label owner (Artikal Music & Lion Charge) from the UK. Known for his minimalistic dark tribal sound in the both the dubstep and drum and bass scenes since 2006.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Following his widely acclaimed breakout moment winning the 2013 DMC World Online Championships, Jon1st quickly built an international reputation as a ‘DJ’s DJ’. Not only proving himself as one of the world’s most diverse and musical turntablists, Jon also established himself as an on the pulse club DJ mixing across the alternative bass music spectrum and as an in demand live performer around the world, as well as recording acclaimed guest mixes for everyone from DJ Mag to Boiler Room to Ninja Tune’s Solid Steel to Mary Anne Hobbs to Keep Hush.

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
